  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Top, tail, peel and dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2024.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2024.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2024.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2024.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2024.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and 15g <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span> <strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong>,<strong> diced carrot</strong>, and half of the <strong>garlic</strong> (save the rest for later) with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and <strong>salt</strong> </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>star anise</strong> and cook for 6-8 min, or until the onion is soft and translucent</p>\n<p>While the onion softens, chop the <strong>black olives</strong> coarsely</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2024.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2024.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2024.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2024.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2024.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the<strong> Knorr </strong><strong>vegetable stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>ground turmeric </strong>(save the rest for later) with 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>yellow stock</strong></p>\n<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>tomato paste </strong>and cook for 1 min, stirring continuously, then add the <strong>yellow stock </strong>and <strong>chopped olives</strong>, and reduce the heat to low</p>\n<p>Cook for 5 min or until reduced by half</p>",
      "order": 3,
